				<text><![CDATA[1 Certify that the Expenditure changed in this bill could not with due regard  to the interest  of the  pupils service be avoided.I Certify total,to the best of my knowledge and belief,the payments entered in this billhave been duly made to the party entitiled receive them with the exception noted below, which exceed the balance of the permanent advance and will be paid on receipt of the money drawn on this bill .Vouchers for all sums above Rs.50 in amount are attached to this bill have these noted below,which will be forwarded as soon as the amounts have been paid .i have as for as possible obtained vouchers for other sums and i am responsible that they have been so cancelled that they cannot uses again .All Bills to be paid by book transfer annexed.

2 Certified that the amount on accounts of pay and allowances of the menials,drawn one month/two month/three months previous to this date with the exceptions of those
detailed below of which the tota amount has been refuned by deduction from this bill have been disbursed to the menials concerned and their receipts taken.

3 Certified that the materials and stores billed for above brought on the respective inventories and that all materials and stores are being duty accounted for and verified in the manner laid down in Articles 133,145,Chennai Financial Code.

4 Certified further that the articles or materials billed for have been purchased on the tender system prescribed in Article 125,Chennai Financial Code and have been received in good order that their quantities are correct and their quality good and according to specifications that the rated paid are not in excess of the accepted and the market rates and that suitable notes of payment have been recorded against the original indents and invoices concerned to prevent double payments.

5 Certified that
    a) The Expenditure on conveyance hire charged in this bill terms of item 11 Appendix 7 to the Chennai Financial Code was actually incurred was unavoidable and is within the schedule scale of charges for the conveyance used and 
    b) The Government servant concerned is not entitiled to draw travelling allowance under the ordinary rules for the journey and he is not granted any compulsory leave and does not and will not otherwise receive any special remuneration for the performance of the duty which necessiated t-lurney.

6 Certified that his menials whose pay has been charged in the bill were actually entertained in Government Service During the period concerned.

7 Certified that in respect of the amount drawn on account of rents,rates and tax is m this m this bill.
	i) No Portion of the building for which the expenditure was incurred and utiliesed for residential or other purpose during the period the charges paid
	ii) The Expenditure in respect of the portion office building used for residential or other purpose during the period for which the charges were paid has been recovered from the under mentioned.Government Servants from whom it was due
	a)The amount drawn on account of rents,rates and taxes etc.,in the previous contigent bill of the type(Number and Date to be given)has actually been paid to the parties on concerned,and 
	b)that the amount drawn in this bill be paid to the parties on realization
8 Certified that the monitory QC quantitative limits prescribed by the government in respect of the items of the contingencies in the bill have not been encoded

9 Certified that the monitory or quantitative limits prescribed by the government in respect of the items of the contingencies in the bill have not been exceeded

10 Certified in respect of pensioner employed as menials whose pay has been charged in this bill such pay has been fixed with reference with paragraph 521 of the chennai pension code and Govt.Memo randum No.8658. Finance (Pension-1) Dated:30-11-1951
	
 ]]></text>
